The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 The International Cricket Council (ICC) will help the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) in the renovation of the scoreboard and the electronic screen at the Eden. In an e-mail, the ICC has made it known that the 2011 World Cup venues needed to improve the facilities ahead of the mega event. The CAB has also decided that as per the norms of the ICC, at least two Ranji Trophy matches will be played at the Eden ahead of the World Cup.      
	In a separate development, the BCCI has directed the state associations to have video analysts for all age groups. Meanwhile, according to sources, former Bengal under-19 coach Gopal Bose will take over the newly formed Bengal U-14 team.          
	 The season for them is yet to begin, but the list of casualties in the East Bengal camp is increasing everyday. After Alvito DCunha (dengue) and Robin Singh (knee injury), new recruit Ekene Ikenwa was admitted at a city hospital after being diagnosed with viral fever.                 
	Football: CFL Premier Division - WB Police vs Peerless (Khardah); Eastern Railway vs Kalighat MS, (Kalyani ). Both matches from 3.30pm                                                                                                                                                      
